== Overview ==

=== General Use ===
Iron tools are generally classified as {{ill|agricultural implements|ja|農機具}}, tools for crafting, or implements related to the production of {{ill|ironware|ja|鉄器}}. However, the tōsu does not fit neatly into these categories and is instead considered a multi-purpose tool. While commonly used as a crafting implement, it also served as a kitchen tool, a {{ill|cosmetic|ja|化粧}} accessory, a {{ill|ritual implement|ja|儀仗}}, or even as a knife for shaving the surface of {{ill|mokkan|ja|木簡}} (wooden tablets used for writing).

